Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.19,0:00:07.40,Location,,0,0,0,,{\fad(700,700)\an8}Reichwein Psychotherapy Center \N(Munich)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.45,0:00:05.00,Default,,0,0,30,,You haven't had a drink since then, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.45,0:00:07.54,Default,,0,0,30,,I haven't. Not one since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.37,0:00:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. As long as you stay away from\Nalcohol, you can get a fresh start.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.00,0:00:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I keep meeting with you once\Na week, I won't be able to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.34,0:00:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid of your thunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.22,0:00:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thunder? What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.93,0:00:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is counseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.27,0:00:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even have time to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.23,0:00:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working on my first important\Ncase since becoming a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.94,0:00:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First case?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.86,0:00:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, what do you make of this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.78,0:00:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.49,0:00:46.91,Note,,0,0,0,,[Note: {\i1}Physiognomy{\i0} is the prediction of a person's\Ncharacteristics based on his facial features.]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.49,0:00:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,With your famous physiognomy,\Ntell me what kind of person he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Physiognomy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.29,0:00:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard, are you confusing me\Nfor a fortune teller?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.88,0:00:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's widely known that you can determine\Na person's personality with a glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.59,0:00:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell what type of personality\Npeople have just by looking at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.76,0:01:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because of my many years of\Nexperience talking to my clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.26,0:01:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So with that experience, can you\Ntell me if he's a crook or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.85,0:01:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A crook?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.23,0:01:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't be. He doesn't have\Nthe face of a swindler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.11,0:01:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the type of guy who would break down\Nif he ever got someone to go for his scam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.03,0:01:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So he could commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.57,0:01:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.37,0:01:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He would not consider suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.41,0:01:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Spoken so firmly... I feel the great persuasive\Npower of your mental abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.42,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all from experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.67,0:01:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So what about that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.46,0:01:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Hans George Schubert.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.76,0:01:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Schubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know of him, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.26,0:01:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.47,0:01:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vampire of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one who hired me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.69,0:02:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The man in the photo, Edmund\NFahren, called himself his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.49,0:02:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he figured out it was a\Nscam right away, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.53,0:02:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Mr. Schubert completely believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.29,0:02:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was quite a clever trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.21,0:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me a lot of work to determine\Nwhether or not he was a fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.96,0:02:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's still one mystery left...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.75,0:02:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he know so much about Schubert's son\Nthat he could make Schubert believe him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.22,0:02:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you ask Edmund himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.81,0:02:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't. He recently committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:06.39,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(700,400)\pos(360,340)}The Secret Woods
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just show me Edmund Fahren's last note.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.10,0:04:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We've checked the handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that he wrote the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to show it to\Nan outsider like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The two witnesses,\NKarl Neuman and Lotte Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They were Fahren's co-workers,\Nweren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They were just friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Just friends," you say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.75,0:04:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as always?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.88,0:04:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we don't have enough men.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.67,0:04:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't had any rest ever\Nsince I took your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.76,0:04:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotten pretty arrogant,\NMartin the Blockhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've asked you to stop calling me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.93,0:04:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not my boss, and I'm not\Nyour subordinate anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now, Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:05:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand the trouble\Nwe went through that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.44,0:05:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent all that time tracking down that serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you shot him in a drunken stupor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know the trouble we had after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I ask you to leave now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time to deal\Nwith a simple suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the scene under control,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really. It wasn't a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.10,0:05:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already given them permission to move out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably moving his\Nbelongings out this very day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When did Martin the Blockhead get so pushy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's going to be a trader coming\Nto pick up his belongings soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So he hung the rope from this pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.97,0:06:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote his last words at this desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was writing an essay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.14,0:06:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Birth of Tragedy."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Assumptions and Reality."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Psychology of the World."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.19,0:06:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like he was a philosophy student.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be what he was writing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is "History of the Gaelic War."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there one unrelated book here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.71,0:06:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Spanish...? No... Latin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't read it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as good as new and looks unused,\Nbut only this part is underlined...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Room 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.97,0:06:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, go get some more boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:06:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put the books in the boxes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you about the person next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told them everything I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a cop. I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care. It's still annoying either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a report to give tomorrow, but thanks to\Nthe ruckus next door, I can't concentrate at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. Let me ask just one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Were these people close to Fahren?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.52,0:07:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but I've never\Nseen them around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.32,0:07:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that he didn't have\Nvery many friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done here, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.68,0:07:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.45,0:07:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:08:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you translate this for me?\NWhere it's underlined...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.83,0:08:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to be responsible\Nfor my bad grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.13,0:08:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,go on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,pretending..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know?\NIsn't that enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,go on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pretending..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that before somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you like it up here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, there. You're Johan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a much better view\Nof the scenery from up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.33,0:09:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.25,0:09:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.21,0:09:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I said stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I said stop it! It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you come here often?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Around this time, all the lights\Nin the houses come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:10:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Families return to their homes and\Nit smells like dinner everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.83,0:10:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what I've always wished for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wished for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I never had that when\NI was a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How is your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I say something to hurt your feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is, ever since I was a boy, I've\Nbeen adopted by foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wouldn't mind, can I ask you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,About your life...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell? This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't go on pretending..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.33,0:10:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They were Fahren's "last words."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.42,0:10:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't his last words at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.75,0:10:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was just translating that\Npassage of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my life story.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little morbid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strange. I feel like I can tell you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.36,0:11:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What you just said... your rich father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you talking about Mr. Schubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.88,0:11:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,crying for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.13,0:11:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.21,0:12:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural that I, someone who takes\Ncare of Mr. Schubert, am worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.18,0:12:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since Fahren's suicide,\Nhe hasn't been eating at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, he'll be the one to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, why don't you tell him that\Nyou're his real son?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.24,0:12:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see what\Nkind of person he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I told him the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.25,0:12:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd just think I was after his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of person Mr. Schubert is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.75,0:12:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Money is everything to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't understand how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.43,0:12:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to do {\i1}something{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.34,0:12:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is suffering in the abyss of despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.54,0:12:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't go on pretending."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter that Fahren left\Nbehind wasn't a suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from this Latin book in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He was just translating the underlined portion\Nfrom this book, "History of the Gaelic War."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that this was not a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.34,0:13:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.14,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just my opinion from working\Non police matters for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.19,0:13:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you listening, Mr. Schubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.40,0:13:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't seem very energetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.71,0:13:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't a suicide, the killer\Nmight be after you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He... He was my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.97,0:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second. I told you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.01,0:14:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,His birthplace and personal history\Ndon't have anything to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that he wasn't a bad person, and he's not the\Nkind of person who would try to bring you misery,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.69,0:14:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but he {\i1}did {\i0} try to trick you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The master is tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.91,0:14:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.04,0:14:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to stop investigating this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just because I don't want to solve\Nmy first case since changing occupations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.05,0:14:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that there's something more\Nmalicious happening here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.72,0:14:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some things you can\Nnever make up for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.19,0:15:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.11,0:15:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I do, so very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.83,0:15:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The search will continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.71,0:15:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A children's bill of rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.42,0:15:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of like an international guarantee of base\Nnorms for the protection of children's rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.06,0:15:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the theme I'm working on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.18,0:15:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm volunteering to take care of\Nthese children, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.73,0:15:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have anything to do with that.\NI'm just doing it because I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.40,0:15:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, lets hear the rest of the story\Nthat you were telling before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.36,0:15:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,about Schubert going bankrupt\Nthree times in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.91,0:15:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each of the three times, he\Ndisappeared for a little while,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:15:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and when he reappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.04,0:16:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he came back with plans to aggressively\Nstart his business again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.59,0:16:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd heard that kind of thing from him while I was\Ndoing my part-time job reading to him on Fridays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.84,0:16:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear about where he went\Nto when he disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.60,0:16:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would be good if we took him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There are places that can make anyone better...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Like when you watch people's homes\Nfrom the school's rooftop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.83,0:16:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kunz,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.79,0:16:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems that one of the sinks in\Nthe bathroom is clogged up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you take a look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.64,0:16:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, what's wrong with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, open up. Don't mess with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.56,0:17:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What is she thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, open up! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.49,0:17:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do with the master?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,His eyes are bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.25,0:17:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is kidnapping! It's kidnapping!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. The plan worked perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.93,0:17:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.39,0:17:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you taking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A good place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.61,0:17:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you aren't Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.86,0:17:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want information on the late Mr. Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.57,0:17:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed up here, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.12,0:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one was Fahren?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.45,0:18:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.33,0:18:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There were two pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.79,0:18:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They both called themselves Schubert's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it the blonde one...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.80,0:18:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or was it the one with black hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Black hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.72,0:18:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The one with black hair came with a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he brought\Na girl to a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He had black hair and was with a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.35,0:18:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.95,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,claimed to be Schubert's son?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.99,0:18:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.95,0:18:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it is. Right around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you brought me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, well... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.13,0:18:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Obenberg Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to... cheer you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.78,0:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see the lake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.43,0:19:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the autumn colors of\Nthe forest beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very much so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.89,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the wrens?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear the calling of the wrens.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.31,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.23,0:19:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is now a construction site.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.70,0:19:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you hear them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They are crying so beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.92,0:20:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Many apples have fallen in the grove.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.22,0:20:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaves catch the setting sun\Nand look as if they are on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.95,0:20:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The lake is so still that\Nit looks like a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.09,0:20:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.05,0:20:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe that such\Na splendid sight exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.13,0:21:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.42,0:21:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.72,0:21:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You said there were two {\i1}pairs{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.68,0:21:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The black-haired one brought a girl with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.97,0:21:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So Fahren didn't come alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.19,0:21:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The blonde one had someone with him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Fahren didn't even talk that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.15,0:22:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The other young man talked in much more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.20,0:22:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.41,0:22:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But if he'd called himself Schubert's\Nson, I would have believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.38,0:22:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.76,0:22:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was he?
